    comment: '<p>You can wrap pieces of text around shapes using <code>shape-outside</code>. As of <code>CSS3</code>, this property only works on elements that have the property of <code>float</code> applied upon it.</p>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-css">#element {\n  float: left;\n  shape-outside: circle(50%);\n  width: 100px;\n  height: 100px;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>This is the visual equivalent of the above snippet:</p>\n<p><svg version="1.2" baseProfile="tiny" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" height="auto" viewBox="0 0 612 200"> <path fill="#596294" stroke="#000" stroke-width=".25" stroke-miterlimit="10" d="M0 0h612v200H0z"/> <circle fill="#FFF" stroke="#000" stroke-width=".25" stroke-miterlimit="10" cx="100" cy="100" r="100"/> <text transform="translate(162.581 22.911)" fill="#FFF" font-family="&#x27;Roboto-Regular&#x27;" font-size="22"> This is how the shape-outside property wraps text </text> <text transform="translate(186 48.511)" fill="#FFF" font-family="&#x27;Roboto-Regular&#x27;" font-size="22"> around the element. This is how the shape- </text> <text transform="translate(197 74.111)" fill="#FFF" font-family="&#x27;Roboto-Regular&#x27;" font-size="22"> outside property wraps text around the </text> <text transform="translate(201.844 99.71)" fill="#FFF" font-family="&#x27;Roboto-Regular&#x27;" font-size="22"> element. This is how the shape-outside </text> <text transform="translate(201.844 125.311)" fill="#FFF" font-family="&#x27;Roboto-Regular&#x27;" font-size="22"> property wraps text around the element. This </text> <text transform="translate(192 150.911)" fill="#FFF" font-family="&#x27;Roboto-Regular&#x27;" font-size="22"> is how the shape-outside property wraps text </text> <text transform="translate(175 176.511)" fill="#FFF" font-family="&#x27;Roboto-Regular&#x27;" font-size="22"> around the element. </text></svg></p>\n<p>Other functions instead of <code>circle()</code> include: <code>ellipse()</code>, <code>polygon()</code>, <code>inset()</code>.</p>\n<p>However, this property is not supported by IE or Firefox and does not change the actual shape of the element.</p>\n',
